-- EON Asks for Bids in $3.8 Billion Gas Network Sale, Reuters Says
-- B y   C o r n e l i u s   R a h n
-- 2012-01-07T13:39:18Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-07/eon-asks-for-bids-in-3-8-billion-gas-network-sale-reuters-says.html
EON AG (EOAN)  has at least five potential
bidder groups for its gas distribution network and is asking
them to indicate interest by Jan. 20, Reuters reported, citing
an unidentified “senior” banker.  The Open Grid Europe asset, which may sell for about 3
billion euros ($3.8 billion), has attracted the interest of
infrastructure funds including Macquarie, GS Infrastructure
Partners and Borealis, plus parties from the  energy industry ,
according to the banking official, Reuters said.  Allianz SE (ALV)  has
teamed up with  Canada ’s CPP Investment Board to bid for the
pipeline operator, Reuters said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cornelius Rahn in Frankfurt at 
 crahn2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
